Anna Marie NORTON, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 9611. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 5, 1941. Rehearing Denied April 2, 1941. S. S. McCahill, of Miami, Fla., for appellant. Fendall Marbury and Keith L. Seegmil-ler, Sp. Attys., Department of Justice, Julius C. Martin, Director, War Risk Litigation, and Wilbur C. Pickett, Sp. Asst, to the Atty. Gen., all of Washington, D. C., and H. S. Phillips, U. S. Atty., of Tampa, Fla., for appellee.

Before FOSTER, HUTCHESON, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

In the above numbered and entitled cause the judgment, 38 F.Supp. 158, is affirmed.
